    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>You are given an array <b>a</b> of size <b>n</b> consisting of non-negative integers. You have to find length of longest subarray of this array such that sum of subarray is even.</p>\n\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>The first line of input contains a single integer <b>T</b> denoting number of test cases</li>\n<li>First line of each test case contains a single integer <b>n</b> denoting the size of array <b>a</b></li>\n<li>Second line of each test case contains <b>n</b> space separated integers denoting the array <b>a</b>.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>For each test case, output a single integer in a line corresponding to the answer of the problem.</li>\n</ul>\n</ul>\n\n\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>1 \u2264 <b>T</b> \u2264 <b>30</b></li>\n<li>0 \u2264 <b>a<sub>i</sub></b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>6</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h3>Subtasks</h3>\n<p>\n<b>Subtask #1 (20 points)</b>\n<ul>\n<li>1 \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>100</b></li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n<b>Subtask #2 (30 points)</b>\n<ul>\n<li>1 \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>3</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<p>\n<b>Subtask #3 (50 points)</b>\n<ul>\n<li>1 \u2264 <b>n</b> \u2264 <b>10<sup>5</sup></b></li>\n</ul>\n</p>\n\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n3\n3\n2 3 4\n2\n2 2\n2\n1 2\n\n<b>Output:</b>\n1\n2\n1\n</pre>\n\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b> Subarray <b>a</b>[1, 1] (i.e. [2]), <b>a</b>[3, 3] (i.e. [4]) are both of even sum. There is no other subarrays having even sum. So the answer is 2.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Example case 2.</b> Sum of 2 + 2 is 4, which is even. Hence answer will be 2.\n</p>\n\n<p><b>Example case 3.</b> There is only a even subarray, <b>a</b>[1, 1], (i.e. 1) which is even. Hence answer will be 2.\n</p>",
